<div class="sd2-blue__lead"><figure><mvt:item name="readytheme" param="image( 'about-sinister-blue' )" /></figure><div><p>Despite what social media may suggest, Sinister Diesel is not suing everyone over the use of blue.</p><p>The United States Patent and Trademark Office issued Sinister Diesel a registration for the color blue as used on aftermarket diesel-performance truck parts for resale. It does not prevent truck owners from painting or customizing parts for personal use.</p><p>The purpose is to reduce customer confusion caused by counterfeit and inferior products presented as genuine Sinister Diesel parts.</p></div></div>
<div class="sd2-blue__faq"><details open><summary>Why trademark blue?</summary><p>To protect the quality reputation associated with Sinister Diesel products and help customers distinguish genuine products from counterfeits.</p></details><details><summary>Why was enforcement necessary?</summary><p>Counterfeit products using a similar blue finish have been mistaken for genuine Sinister Diesel parts, including products presented for returns or support.</p></details><details><summary>Are truck owners affected?</summary><p>No. Owners can paint a truck or create blue parts for personal use. The registration concerns blue aftermarket parts for light-duty diesel engines intended for resale.</p></details><details><summary>Does this apply to factory parts?</summary><p>No. It does not apply to stock components or products outside the registered aftermarket diesel-performance category.</p></details><details><summary>Can a color be protected as a trademark?</summary><p>Yes. Color can identify a source when customers associate it with a brand. The registration uses ordinary color language even when a commercial color system is also supplied.</p></details><details><summary>Where can I review the registration?</summary><p>Review the public <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="https://tsdr.uspto.gov/#caseNumber=87840011&caseSearchType=US_APPLICATION&caseType=DEFAULT&searchType=statusSearch">USPTO trademark record</a> for the current status and documents.</p></details></div>
<div class="sd2-blue__comparisons"><figure><mvt:item name="readytheme" param="image( 'genuine-vs-counterfeit-1' )" /><figcaption>Genuine Sinister part compared with a counterfeit example.</figcaption></figure><figure><mvt:item name="readytheme" param="image( 'genuine-vs-counterfeit-2' )" /><figcaption>Use markings, finish, packaging and seller history together.</figcaption></figure></div>
